en_142035_0	Democratic Left Front leader Vasudeva Nanayakkara says that the Government had taken no action to re-erect the monument that was removed by the Urban Development Authority during the previous regime.
en_142035_1	The monument was erected by his party in remembrance of persons killed during the war.
en_142035_2	The DLF leader said that the monument had been removed following a directive from the former secretary of the Defence and Urban Development Authority, saying at the time, that it would to be relocated.
en_142035_3	The monument had been position close to the Battaramulla junction leading to parliament.
en_142035_4	MP Nanayakkara said that the current Government had not taken measures to achieve this.
